main event: A witness observed an unidentified luminous round object at high altitude in Glen Ellyn, Illinois on July 1, 1963.
interesting points: The object appeared to move from 140 to 160 azimuth to the west, and was observed again during November and December.
The witness reported that the object seemed much brighter than any planet they had ever seen, with remarkable clarity.
The object disappeared behind some trees at one point, then reappeared, leading the witness to believe it was the same object they had been observing.
The object appeared to be larger than a typical aircraft, covering a considerable portion of the sky.
The witness described the object as round, luminous, and leaving a trail of light or vapor in the sky while being observed.
